obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (19321)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00003_200530_1517807317795&sectionId=19321&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00003_200530_1517807317795
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Credit Information`
  line `Companies (Regulation) Act, 2005.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date ^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint:`
  line
  line `Provided that different dates may be appointed for different provisions of this Act, and any reference`
  line `in any such provision to the commencement of this Act shall be construed as a reference to the coming`
  line `into force of that provision.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 14th December, 2006, vide notification No. S.O. 2098(E), dated 14th December, 2006, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary,`
  line `Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (19322)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00003_200530_1517807317795&sectionId=19322&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00003_200530_1517807317795
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "board" means the Board of directors of a credit information company;`
  line
  line `(b) "borrower" means any person who has been granted loan or any other credit facility by a`
  line `credit institution and includes a client of a credit institution;`
  line
  line `(c) "client" includes--`
  line
  line `(i) a guarantor or a person who proposes to give guarantee or security for a borrower of a`
  line `credit institution; or`
  line
  line `(ii) a person--`
  line
  line `(A) who has obtained or seeks to obtain financial assistance from a credit institution, by`
  line `way of loans, advances, hire purchase, leasing facility, letter of credit, guarantee facility,`
  line `venture capital assistance or by way of credit cards or in any other form or manner;`
  line
  line `(B) who has raised or seeks to raise money by issue of security as defined in clause (h) of`
  line `section 2 of the Securities Contracts (Regulation) Act, 1956 (42 of 1956), or by issue of`
  line `commercial paper, depository receipt or any other instrument;`
  line
  line `(C) whose financial standing has been assessed or is proposed to be assessed by a credit`
  line `institution or any other person or institution as may, by notification, be directed by the`
  line `Reserve Bank;`
  line
  line `(d) "credit information" means any information relating to--`
  line
  line `(i) the amounts and the nature of loans or advances, amounts outstanding under credit cards`
  line `and other credit facilities granted or to be granted, by a credit institution to any borrower;`
  line
  line `(ii) the nature of security taken or proposed to be taken by a credit institution from any`
  line `borrower for credit facilities granted or proposed to be granted to him;`
  line
  line `(iii) the guarantee furnished or any other non-fund based facility granted or proposed to be`
  line `granted by a credit institution for any of its borrowers;`
  line
  line `(iv) the credit worthiness of any borrower of a credit institution;`
  line
  line `(v) any other matter which the Reserve Bank may, consider necessary for inclusion in the`
  line `credit information to be collected and maintained by credit information companies, and, specify,`
  line `by notification, in this behalf;`
  line
  line `(e) "credit information company" means a company formed and registered under the Companies`
  line `Act, 1956 (1 of 1956) and which has been granted a certificate of registration under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 5;`
  line
  line `(f) "credit institution" means a banking company and includes--`
  line
  line `(i) a corresponding new bank, the State Bank of India, a subsidiary bank, a co-operative bank,`
  line `the National Bank and regional rural bank;`
  line
  line `(ii) a non-banking financial company as defined under clause (f) of section 45-I of the`
  line `Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934);`
  line
  line `(iii) a public financial institution referred to in section 4A of the Companies Act,`
  line `1956 (1 of 1956);`
  line
  line `(iv) the financial corporation established by a State under section 3 of the State Financial`
  line `Corporation Act, 1951 (63 of 1951);`
  line
  line `(v) the housing finance institution referred to in clause (d) of section 2 of the National`
  line `Housing Bank Act, 1987 (53 of 1987);`
  line
  line `(vi) the companies engaged in the business of credit cards and other similar cards and`
  line `companies dealing with distribution of credit in any other manner;`
  line
  line `(vii) any other institution which the Reserve Bank may specify, from time to time, for the`
  line `purposes of this clause;`
  line
  line `(g) "credit scoring" means a system which enables a credit institution to assess the credit`
  line `worthiness and capacity of a borrower to repay his loan and advances and discharge his other`
  line `obligations in respect of credit facility availed or to be availed by him;`
  line
  line `(h) "notification" means a notification published in the Official Gazette of India;`
  line
  line `(i) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(j) "regulations" means regulations made by the Reserve Bank under this Act;`
  line
  line `(k) "Reserve Bank" means the Reserve Bank of India constituted under section 3 of the Reserve`
  line `Bank of India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934);`
  line
  line `(l) "specified user" means any credit institution, credit information company being a member`
  line `under sub-section (3) of section 15, and includes such other person or institution as may be specified`
  line `by regulations made, from time to time, by the Reserve Bank for the purpose of obtaining credit`
  line `information from a credit information company;`
  line
  line `(m) words and expressions used herein and not defined in this Act but defined in the Reserve`
  line `Bank of India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934) or the Banking Regulation Act, 1949 (10 of 1949) or the`
  line `Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956) shall have the meanings respectively assigned to them in those`
  line Acts.
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (19323)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Prohibition to commence or carry on business of credit information.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00003_200530_1517807317795&sectionId=19323&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00003_200530_1517807317795
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `Save as otherwise`
  line `provided in this Act, no company shall commence or carry on the business of credit information without`
  line `obtaining a certificate of registration from the Reserve Bank under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (19324)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Application for registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00003_200530_1517807317795&sectionId=19324&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00003_200530_1517807317795
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every company which intends to commence the business of`
  line `credit information shall make an application for registration to the Reserve Bank in such form and manner`
  line `as may be specified by regulations.`
  line
  line `(2) Every credit information company, in existence on the commencement of this Act, before the`
  line `expiry of six months from such commencement, shall apply in writing to the Reserve Bank for obtaining`
  line `a certificate of registration under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the case of a credit information company in existence on the commencement of this`
  line `Act, nothing in section 3 shall be deemed to prohibit such credit information company from carrying on`
  line `the business of a credit information company, until it is granted a certificate of registration or is by notice`
  line `in writing informed by the Reserve Bank that a certificate of registration cannot be granted to it.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (19325)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Grant of certificate of registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00003_200530_1517807317795&sectionId=19325&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00003_200530_1517807317795
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Reserve Bank may, for the purpose of considering`
  line `the application of a company for grant of a certificate of registration to commence or carry on the`
  line `business of credit information, require to be satisfied, by an inspection of records or books of such`
  line `company or otherwise that the following conditions are fulfilled, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) that the applicant company has minimum capital structure referred to in section 8;`
  line
  line `(b) that the general character of the management or the proposed management of the applicant`
  line `company shall not be prejudicial to the interest of its specified users, clients or borrowers, or other`
  line `credit information companies;`
  line
  line `(c) that any other condition, the fulfilment of which in the opinion of the Reserve Bank, shall be`
  line `necessary to ensure that the commencement or carrying on of the business of credit information by`
  line `the applicant company shall not be detrimental or prejudicial to the public interest or banking policy`
  line `or credit system or its specified users or clients or borrowers or other credit information companies or`
  line `others who would provide credit information to the credit information companies.`
  line
  line `(2) The Reserve Bank may, after being satisfied that the conditions as referred to in sub-section (1)`
  line `are fulfilled, grant a certificate of registration to the applicant company to commence or carry on the`
  line `business of credit information, subject to such conditions which it may consider fit to impose and if the`
  line `company fails to fulfil any of such conditions or any of the provisions of this Act, the application of the`
  line `company shall be rejected:`
  line
  line `Provided that no application shall be rejected unless the applicant has been given an opportunity of`
  line `being heard.`
  line
  line `(3) The Reserve Bank may, having regard to the available business of credit information, the potential`
  line `and scope for expansion of existing credit information companies and other relevant factors, determine`
  line `the total number of the credit information companies which may be granted the certificates of registration`
  line `for carrying on the business of credit information:`
  line
  line `Provided that the total number of such credit information companies so determined may, on being`
  line `satisfied by the Reserve Bank, that there is change in available business of credit information, potential`
  line `and scope for expansion of existing credit information companies and other relevant factors relating`
  line `thereto, be reviewed by the Reserve Bank.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (19326)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Power of Reserve Bank to cancel certificate of registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00003_200530_1517807317795&sectionId=19326&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00003_200530_1517807317795
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Reserve Bank may cancel`
  line `a certificate of registration granted to a credit information company under sub-section (2) of section 5 if`
  line `such company,--`
  line
  line `(i) ceases to carry on the business of credit information; or`
  line
  line `(ii) has failed to comply with any of the conditions subject to which the certificate of registration`
  line `has been granted to it; or`
  line
  line `(iii) at any time fails to fulfil any of the conditions referred to in sub-clauses (a) to (c) of`
  line `sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) of section 5; or`
  line
  line `(iv) fails--`
  line
  line `(a) to comply with the provisions of any law for the time being in force or any direction`
  line `issued by the Reserve Bank under the provisions of this Act; or`
  line
  line `(b) to submit or offer for inspection its books of account and other relevant documents when`
  line `so demanded by the officers, persons or agency referred to in sub-section (1) of section 12.`
  line
  line `(2) Before cancelling the certificate of registration granted to a credit information company under this`
  line `section on the ground that the company has failed to comply with the conditions specified in clauses (a) to`
  line `(c) of sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) of section 5 or the provisions of any other law for the time being`
  line `in force or directions issued under this Act, the Reserve Bank, shall grant time to such company on such`
  line `terms as the Reserve Bank may deem appropriate for taking necessary steps to comply with such`
  line `directions or provisions or fulfilment of such conditions, within such time:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the Reserve Bank is of the opinion that the delay in cancelling the certificate of`
  line `registration of such company shall be prejudicial or detrimental to the public interest or banking policy or`
  line `credit system or borrowers or other credit information companies, the Reserve Bank may cancel the`
  line `certificate of registration without granting time as provided in sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(3) No order of cancellation of certificate of registration, granted to a credit information company,`
  line `shall be made by the Reserve Bank unless such company has been given a reasonable opportunity of`
  line `being heard.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (19327)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Appeal against order of Reserve Bank.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00003_200530_1517807317795&sectionId=19327&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00003_200530_1517807317795
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) A credit information company aggrieved by the`
  line `order of rejection of an application for grant of certificate of registration under section 5 or cancellation of`
  line `certificate of registration under section 6, may prefer an appeal to the Central Government or any other`
  line `authority or tribunal which may be designated by rules made by the Central Government, within a period`
  line `of thirty days from the date on which such order of rejection or cancellation, as the case may be, is`
  line `communicated to the credit information company.`
  line
  line `(2) The decision of the Central Government or the authority or tribunal referred to in sub-section (1)`
  line `where an appeal has been preferred to it under sub-section (1), or of these Reserve Bank where no such`
  line `appeal has been preferred, shall be final:`
  line
  line `Provided that before making any order of rejection of an appeal, the applicant company or the credit`
  line `information company, as the case may be, shall be given a reasonable opportunity of being heard.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (19328)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Requirement as to minimum capital.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00003_200530_1517807317795&sectionId=19328&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00003_200530_1517807317795
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) The authorised capital of every credit information`
  line `company shall be a minimum of thirty crores:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Reserve Bank may, by notification, increase the minimum amount of authorised`
  line `capital to any amount not exceeding fifty crores.`
  line
  line `(2) The issued capital of every credit information company shall not be less than twenty crores:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Reserve Bank may, by notification, increase the issued capital to any amount not`
  line `exceeding the minimum amount of authorised capital as referred to in sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) The minimum paid up capital of every credit information company at any time shall not be less`
  line `than seventy-five per cent. of the issued capital.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (19329)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Management of credit information company.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00003_200530_1517807317795&sectionId=19329&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00003_200530_1517807317795
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in any`
  line `law for the time being in force, or in any contract to the contrary, every credit information company in`
  line `existence on the commencement of this Act, or which comes into existence thereafter, shall have one of`
  line `its directors, who may be appointed on whole-time or on a part-time basis as chairperson of its board, and`
  line `where he is appointed on whole-time basis as chairperson of its board, he shall be entrusted with the`
  line `management of the whole of the affairs of the credit information company:`
  line
  line `Provided that the chairperson of the board of the credit information company shall exercise his`
  line `powers subject to the superintendence, control and directions of the board.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a chairperson is appointed on a part-time basis, the management of whole of the affairs of`
  line `the credit information company shall be entrusted to a managing director or, a whole-time director by`
  line `whatever name called, who shall exercise his powers subject to the superintendence, control and`
  line `directions of the board.`
  line
  line `(3) In addition to the chairperson or managing director or whole-time director, by whatever name`
  line `called, the board of directors shall consist of not less than fifty per cent. directors who shall be persons having special knowledge in, or practical experience of, the matters relating to public administration, law,`
  line `banking, finance, accountancy, management or information technology.`
  line
  line `(4) In discharging its functions, the board shall act on business principles and shall have due regard to`
  line `the interest of its specified users, credit institutions or the clients or borrowers of credit institutions.`
  line
  line `(5) Where the Reserve Bank is satisfied that it is in the public interest or in the interest of banking`
  line `policy or credit system of the country, or for preventing the affairs of any credit information company`
  line `being managed in a manner detrimental to the interest of banking policy or credit institutions or borrowers`
  line `or clients or for securing the proper management of any credit information company, it is necessary so to`
  line `do, the Reserve Bank may, for reasons to be recorded in writing, by order published in the Official`
  line `Gazette, supersede the board of such company, for such period not exceeding six months, as may be`
  line `specified in the order and which may be extended from time to time, so, however, that the total period`
  line `shall not exceed twelve months:`
  line
  line `Provided that before making any such order, the Reserve Bank shall give a reasonable opportunity to`
  line `the board of such credit information company to make representation against the proposed supersession`
  line `and shall consider the representation, if any, of the board.`
  line
  line `(6) The Reserve Bank may, on supersession of the board of a credit information company under subsection`
  line `(5), appoint an Administrator for such period and on such salary and other terms and conditions as`
  line `it may determine.`
  line
  line `(7) The Reserve Bank may issue such directions to the Administrator as it may deem appropriate and`
  line `the Administrator shall be bound to follow such directions.`
  line
  line `(8) Upon making of the order under sub-section (5), superseding the board of a credit information`
  line company--
  line
  line `(a) the chairperson, managing director and other directors of such credit information company`
  line `shall, as from the date of supersession, vacate their offices as such;`
  line
  line `(b) all the powers, functions and duties which may, by or under the provisions of the Companies`
  line `Act, 1956 (1 of 1956) or this Act or any other law for the time being in force, be exercised or`
  line `discharged, by or on behalf of the board of such credit information company, or by a resolution`
  line `passed in general meeting of that company, shall, until the reconstitution of its board under`
  line `sub-section (10), be exercised and discharged by the Administrator appointed by the Reserve Bank`
  line `under sub-section (6):`
  line
  line `Provided that the powers exercised by the Administrator shall be valid notwithstanding that such`
  line `powers are exercisable by a resolution passed in the general meeting of such credit information company.`
  line
  line `(9) The salary and allowances payable to the Administrator and staff assisting the Administrator shall`
  line `be borne by the credit information company.`
  line
  line `(10) On and before the expiration of two months before expiry of the period of supersession`
  line `mentioned in the order of the Reserve Bank issued under sub-section (5), the Administrator of the credit`
  line `information company, shall call a general meeting of the credit information company to elect new`
  line `directors and reconstitute its board and any person who had vacated his office under clause (a) of`
  line `sub-section (8), shall not be deemed to be disqualified for re-appointment.`
  line
  line `(11) Notwithstanding anything contained in any law for the time being in force or in any contract or`
  line `the memorandum or articles of association, of the credit information company, on the removal of a person`
  line `from office under this section, that person shall not be entitled to claim any compensation for the loss or`
  line `termination of office.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (19330)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Power of Reserve Bank to determine policy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00003_200530_1517807317795&sectionId=19330&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00003_200530_1517807317795
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `Where the Reserve Bank is satisfied that it is`
  line `necessary or expedient in the public interest or in the interest of specified users or in the interest of credit`
  line `information companies or credit institutions or clients or borrowers so to do, it may determine the policy`
  line `in relation to functioning of credit information companies or credit institutions or specified users`
  line `generally or in particular and when the policy has been so determined all credit information companies,`
  line `credit institutions and specified users, as the case may be, shall be bound to follow the policy as so`
  line determined.
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (19331)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Power of Reserve Bank to give directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00003_200530_1517807317795&sectionId=19331&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00003_200530_1517807317795
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the Reserve Bank is satisfied that,--`
  line
  line `(a) in the public interest; or`
  line
  line `(b) in the interest of credit institutions; or`
  line
  line `(c) in the interest of specified users; or`
  line
  line `(d) in the interest of banking policy; or`
  line
  line `(e) to prevent the affairs of any credit information company being conducted in a manner`
  line `detrimental to the interests of its specified users or in a manner prejudicial to the interests of credit`
  line `institutions or borrowers or clients; or`
  line
  line `(f) to secure the proper management of credit information companies generally,`
  line
  line `it is necessary to issue directions to credit information companies or credit institutions or specified users`
  line `generally or to any credit information company or credit institution or specified user in particular, it may,`
  line `from time to time, issue such directions as it deems fit, and such credit information companies, credit`
  line `institutions and specified users or credit information company, credit institution, and specified user, as the`
  line `case may be, shall be bound to comply with such directions.`
  line
  line `(2) The Reserve Bank may, on representation made to it or on its own motion, modify or cancel any`
  line `direction issued under sub-section (1), and the Reserve Bank, in so modifying or cancelling any direction,`
  line `may impose such conditions as it thinks fit, subject to which the modification or cancellation shall have`
  line effect.
  line
  line `(3) The Reserve Bank may, at any time, if it is satisfied that in the public interest or in the interest of a`
  line `credit information company or its members, it is necessary so to do, by order in writing and on such terms`
  line `and conditions as may be specified therein,--`
  line
  line `(a) require such credit information company to call a meeting of its directors for the purpose of`
  line `considering any matter relating to or arising out of the affairs of the credit information company;`
  line
  line `(b) depute one or more of its officers to watch the proceedings at any meeting of the board of the`
  line `credit information company or of any committee or of any other body constituted by it and require the`
  line `credit information company to give an opportunity to the officers so deputed to be heard at such`
  line `meetings and also require such officers to send a report of such proceedings to the Reserve Bank;`
  line
  line `(c) require the board of the credit information company or of any committee or any other body`
  line `constituted by it to give in writing to any officer deputed by the Reserve Bank in this behalf at his`
  line `usual address all notices of, and other communications relating to, any meeting of the board,`
  line `committee or other body constituted by it;`
  line
  line `(d) appoint one or more of its officers to observe the manner in which the affairs of the credit`
  line `information company or of its offices or branches are being conducted and make a report thereon;`
  line
  line `(e) require the credit information company to make, within such time as may be specified in the`
  line `order, such changes in the management as the Reserve Bank may consider necessary.`
  line
  line `(4) The Reserve Bank may, at any time, direct any credit information company to furnish it within`
  line `such time as may be specified by the Reserve Bank, such statements and information relating to the`
  line `business or affairs of the credit information company as the Reserve Bank may consider necessary or`
  line `expedient to obtain for the purpose of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (19332)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Inspection of credit information company, credit institution and specified user.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00003_200530_1517807317795&sectionId=19332&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00003_200530_1517807317795
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in section 235 of the Companies Act,`
  line `1956 (1 of 1956), the Reserve Bank, at any time, may and on being directed so to do by the Central`
  line `Government shall, cause an inspection to be made, by one or more of its officers or through such other`
  line `persons or agency as the Reserve Bank may determine, of any credit information company or credit`
  line `institution or specified user and their books and accounts; and the Reserve Bank shall supply to the credit`
  line `information company or credit institution or specified user, as the case may be, a copy of its report on`
  line `such inspection.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall be the duty of every director or other officer or employee of the credit information`
  line `company, credit institution and specified user to produce to any officer or person or agency, as the case may be, making an inspection under sub-section (1) all such books, accounts and other documents in his`
  line `custody or power and to furnish him with any statement and information relating to the affairs of such`
  line `credit information company, credit institution and specified user, as the said officer or person or agency`
  line `may require of him within such time as the said officer or person or agency may specify.`
  line
  line `(3) Any officer of the Reserve Bank or person or an agency making an inspection under`
  line `sub-section (1) may examine on oath any director or other officer or employee of the credit information`
  line `company, credit institution and specified user, in relation to their business, and may administer an oath`
  line accordingly.
  line
  line `(4) The expenses of, or incidental to, the inspection under sub-section (1) by any person or an agency`
  line `referred to in sub-section (1) shall be borne by the concerned credit information company or credit`
  line `institution or specified user, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (19333)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Powers and duties of auditors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00003_200530_1517807317795&sectionId=19333&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00003_200530_1517807317795
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) It shall be the duty of an auditor of a credit information`
  line `company to inquire whether or not the credit information company has furnished to the Reserve Bank`
  line `such statements, information or particulars relating to its business as are required to be furnished under`
  line `this Act and the auditor shall, except where he is satisfied on such inquiry that the credit information`
  line `company has furnished such a statement , information or particulars, make a report to the Reserve Bank in`
  line `this regard.`
  line
  line `(2) The Reserve Bank may, on being satisfied that it is necessary so to do, in the public interest or in`
  line `the interest of credit system, issue directions in particular or in general with respect to audit of the credit`
  line `information company and submission of the report to the Reserve Bank.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the Reserve Bank is of the opinion that it is necessary so to do in the public interest or in`
  line `the interest of the credit information company or its members, or in the interest of credit system or credit`
  line `institution or its borrower or client so to do, it may, at any time, by an order, direct that a special audit of`
  line `the accounts of the credit information company in relation to any such transaction or class of transactions`
  line `or for such period or periods, as may be mentioned in the order, shall be conducted and the Reserve Bank`
  line `may by such order or by a separate order either appoint an auditor or auditors or direct the auditor of the`
  line `credit information company himself to conduct such special audit and the auditor shall comply with such`
  line `directions and make a report of such audit to the Reserve Bank and forward a copy thereof to the credit`
  line `information company.`
  line
  line `(4) The remuneration of the auditors as may be fixed by the Reserve Bank, having regard to the`
  line `nature and volume of work involved in the audit and the expenses of, or incidental to, the audit, shall be`
  line `borne by the credit information company so audited.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (19334)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Functions of a credit information company.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00003_200530_1517807317795&sectionId=19334&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00003_200530_1517807317795
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) A credit information company may engage in`
  line `any one or more of the following forms of business, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) to collect, process and collate information on trade, credit and financial standing of the`
  line `borrowers of the credit institution which is a member of the credit information company;`
  line
  line `(b) to provide credit information to its specified users or to the specified users of any other credit`
  line `information company or to any other credit information company being its member;`
  line
  line `(c) to provide credit scoring to its specified users or specified users of any other credit`
  line `information company or to other credit information companies being its members;`
  line
  line `(d) to undertake research project;`
  line
  line `(e) to undertake any other form of business which the Reserve Bank may, specify by regulations`
  line `as a form of business in which it is lawful for a credit information company to engage.`
  line
  line `(2) No credit information company shall engage in any form of business other than those referred to`
  line `in sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) Any credit information company for the purposes of carrying on the business of credit information`
  line may--
  line
  line `(a) register credit institutions and other credit information companies, at their option as its`
  line `member, subject to such terms and conditions as may be pre-determined and disclosed by such credit`
  line `information company;`
  line
  line `(b) charge such reasonable amount of fees, as it may deem appropriate not exceeding the`
  line `maximum fee, as may be specified under section 27, for furnishing credit information to a specified`
  line user;
  line
  line `(c) generally to do all such other acts and perform such other functions as are necessary to`
  line `facilitate proper conduct of its affairs, business and functions in accordance with the provisions of this`
  line Act.
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (19335)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Credit institution to be member of a credit information company.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00003_200530_1517807317795&sectionId=19335&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00003_200530_1517807317795
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every credit`
  line `institution in existence on the commencement of this Act, before the expiry of three months from such`
  line `commencement or within such extended period, as the Reserve Bank may allow on its application and`
  line `subject to being satisfied about the reason for extension, shall become member of at least one credit`
  line `information company.`
  line
  line `(2) Every credit institution which comes into existence after the commencement of this Act, before`
  line `the expiry of three months from its coming into existence, or within such extended period, as the Reserve`
  line `Bank may allow on its application and subject to being satisfied about the reason for extension, shall`
  line `become member of at least one credit information company.`
  line
  line `(3) A credit information company may, at its option, become member of another credit information`
  line company.
  line
  line `(4) No credit information company shall refuse to register a credit institution or another credit`
  line `information company as its member without providing reasonable opportunity of being heard to such`
  line `credit institution or credit information company, whose application it proposes to reject and recording`
  line `reasons for such rejection and a copy of such order of rejection shall be forwarded to the Reserve Bank.`
  line
  line `(5) A credit institution or credit information company aggrieved by the order of rejection of its`
  line `application for its registration as a member of a credit information company under sub-section (4) may`
  line `prefer an appeal to the Reserve Bank, within a period of thirty days from the date on which such order of`
  line `rejection was communicated to it:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Reserve Bank may, if it is satisfied that the appellant was prevented by sufficient`
  line `cause from filing the appeal within the said period, allow it to be filed within a further period not`
  line `exceeding thirty days.`
  line
  line `(6) On receipt of an appeal under sub-section (5), the Reserve Bank, after giving the appellant and`
  line `other concerned parties, an opportunity of being heard, pass such order as it deems fit.`
  line
  line `(7) The decision of the Reserve Bank where an appeal has been preferred to it under sub-section (5)`
  line `shall be final and the order of the credit information company under sub-section (4) shall be final after the`
  line `expiry of the said period of thirty days where no appeal has been preferred under that sub-section to the`
  line `Reserve Bank.`
  line
  line `(8) Every specified user shall be entitled to obtain credit information for its use from the credit`
  line `information company of which such specified user is a member.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (19336)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Failure to become a member of a credit information company.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00003_200530_1517807317795&sectionId=19336&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00003_200530_1517807317795
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a credit`
  line institution--
  line
  line `(a) abstains from becoming a member of at least one credit information company; or`
  line
  line `(b) at any time is not a member of any credit information company,`
  line
  line `the Reserve Bank suo moto or on a complaint from a credit information company may, direct such credit`
  line `institution to take necessary steps within such time, as it may specify to become a member of a credit`
  line `information company.`
  line
  line `(2) In case a credit institution fails to comply with the directions of the Reserve Bank under`
  line `sub-section (1), to become member of at least one credit information company, the Reserve Bank may,`
  line `without prejudice to the provisions of this Act, intimate such failure to any other authority for taking such`
  line `action as it may deem fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (19337)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Collection and furnishing of credit information.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00003_200530_1517807317795&sectionId=19337&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00003_200530_1517807317795
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) A credit information company or any`
  line `person authorised in that behalf by the company may, by notice in writing, in such form, as may be`
  line `specified by regulations made by the Reserve Bank or as near thereto, require its members being credit`
  line `institution or credit information company, to furnish such credit information as it may deem necessary in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every credit institution which is member of the credit information company and every credit`
  line `information company which is a member of other credit information company shall, on receipt of notice`
  line `under sub-section (1), provide credit information to the credit information company of which it is a`
  line `member, within such period as may be specified in the notice.`
  line
  line `(3) Every credit information company shall provide for such purpose, as may be specified by`
  line `regulations, the credit information received under sub-section (2), to its specified user on receipt of`
  line `request from him in accordance with the provisions of this Act and directions issued thereunder by the`
  line `Reserve Bank from time to time in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(4) No credit information received under this Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) by the credit information company, shall be disclosed to any person other than its specified`
  line `user; or`
  line
  line `(b) by the specified user, shall be disclosed to any other person;`
  line
  line `(c) by the credit information company or specified user, shall be disclosed for any other purpose`
  line `than as permitted or required by any other law for the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (19338)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Settlement of dispute.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00003_200530_1517807317795&sectionId=19338&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00003_200530_1517807317795
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in any law for the time being in`
  line `force, if any dispute arises amongst, credit information companies, credit institutions, borrowers and`
  line `clients on matters relating to business of credit information and for which no remedy has been provided`
  line `under this Act, such disputes shall be settled by conciliation or arbitration as provided in the Arbitration`
  line `and Conciliation Act, 1996 (26 of 1996), as if the parties to the dispute have consented in writing for`
  line `determination of such dispute by conciliation or arbitration and provisions of that Act shall apply`
  line accordingly.
  line
  line `(2) Where a dispute has been referred to arbitration under sub-section (1), the same shall be settled or`
  line decided,--
  line
  line `(a) by the arbitrator to be appointed by the Reserve Bank;`
  line
  line `(b) within three months of making a reference by the parties to the dispute:`
  line
  line `Provided that the arbitrator may, after recording the reasons therefor, extend the said period up to a`
  line `maximum period of six months:`
  line
  line `Provided further that, in an appropriate case or cases, the Reserve Bank may, if it considers necessary`
  line `to do so (reasons to be recorded in writing), direct the parties to the dispute to appoint an arbitrator in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of the Arbitration and Conciliation Act, 1996 (26 of 1996), for settlement`
  line `of their dispute in accordance with the provisions of that Act.`
  line
  line `(3) Save as otherwise provided under this Act, the provisions of the Arbitration and Conciliation Act,`
  line `1996 (26 of 1996) shall apply to all arbitration under this Act as if the proceedings for arbitration were`
  line `referred for settlement or decision under the provisions of the Arbitration and Conciliation Act, 1996.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (19339)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Accuracy and security of credit information.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00003_200530_1517807317795&sectionId=19339&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00003_200530_1517807317795
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `A credit information company or credit`
  line `institution or specified user, as the case may be, in possession or control of credit information, shall take`
  line `such steps (including security safeguards) as may be prescribed, to ensure that the data relating to the credit information maintained by them is accurate, complete, duly protected against any loss or`
  line `unauthorised access or use or unauthorised disclosure thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (19340)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Privacy principles.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00003_200530_1517807317795&sectionId=19340&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00003_200530_1517807317795
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `Every credit information company, credit institution and specified user,`
  line `shall adopt the following privacy principles in relation to collection, processing, collating, recording,`
  line `preservation, secrecy, sharing and usage of credit information, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the principles--`
  line
  line `(i) which may be followed by every credit institution for collection of information from its`
  line `borrowers and clients and by every credit information company, for collection of information`
  line `from its member credit institutions or credit information companies, for processing, recording,`
  line `protecting the data relating to credit information furnished by, or obtained from, their member`
  line `credit institutions or credit information companies, as the case may be, and sharing of such data`
  line `with specified users;`
  line
  line `(ii) which may be adopted by every specified user for processing, recording, preserving and`
  line `protecting the data relating to credit information furnished, or received, as the case may be, by it;`
  line
  line `(iii) which may be adopted by every credit information company for allowing access to`
  line `records containing credit information of borrowers and clients and alteration of such records in`
  line `case of need to do so;`
  line
  line `(b) the purpose for which the credit information may be used, restriction on such use and`
  line `disclosure thereof;`
  line
  line `(c) the extent of obligation to check accuracy of credit information before furnishing of such`
  line `information to credit information companies or credit institutions or specified users, as the case may`
  line be;
  line
  line `(d) preservation of credit information maintained by every credit information company, credit`
  line `institution, and specified user as the case may be (including the period for which such information`
  line `may be maintained, manner of deletion of such information and maintenance of records of credit`
  line `information);`
  line
  line `(e) networking of credit information companies, credit institutions and specified users through`
  line `electronic mode;`
  line
  line `(f) any other principles and procedures relating to credit information which the Reserve Bank may`
  line `consider necessary and appropriate and may be specified by regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (19341)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Alteration of credit information files and credit reports.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00003_200530_1517807317795&sectionId=19341&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00003_200530_1517807317795
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person, who applies for`
  line `grant or sanction of credit facility, from any credit institution, may request to such institution to furnish`
  line `him a copy of the credit information obtained by such institution from the credit information company.`
  line
  line `(2) Every credit institution shall, on receipt of request under sub-section (1), furnish to the person`
  line `referred to in that sub-section a copy of the credit information subject to payment of such charges, as may`
  line `be specified by regulations, by the Reserve Bank in this regard.`
  line
  line `(3) If a credit information company or specified user or credit institution in possession or control of`
  line `the credit information, has not updated the information maintained by it, a borrower or client may request`
  line `all or any of them to update the information; whether by making an appropriate correction, or addition or`
  line `otherwise, and on such request the credit information company or the specified user or the credit`
  line `institution, as the case may be, shall take appropriate steps to update the credit information within thirty`
  line `days after being requested to do so:`
  line
  line `Provided that the credit information company and the specified user shall make the correction,`
  line `deletion or addition in the credit information only after such correction, deletion or addition has been`
  line `certified as correct by the concerned credit institution:`
  line
  line `Provided further that no such correction, deletion or addition shall be made in the credit information if`
  line `any dispute relating to such correction, deletion or addition is pending before any arbitrator or tribunal or`
  line `court and in cases where such dispute is pending, the entries in the books of the concerned credit`
  line `institution shall be taken into account for the purpose of credit information.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (19342)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Unauthorised access to credit information.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00003_200530_1517807317795&sectionId=19342&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00003_200530_1517807317795
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person shall have access to credit`
  line `information in the possession or control of a credit information company or a credit institution or a`
  line `specified user unless the access is authorised by this Act or any other law for the time being in force or`
  line `directed to do so by any court or tribunal and any such access to credit information without such`
  line `authorisation or direction shall be considered as an unauthorised access to credit information.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person who obtains unauthorised access to credit information as referred to in sub-section (1)`
  line `shall be punishable with fine which may extend to one lakh rupees in respect of each offence and if he`
  line `continues to have such unauthorised access, with further fine which may extend to ten thousand rupees`
  line `for every day on which the default continues and such unauthorised credit information shall not be taken`
  line `into account for any purpose.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (19343)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Offences and penalties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00003_200530_1517807317795&sectionId=19343&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00003_200530_1517807317795
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever, in any return or other document or in any information`
  line `required or furnished by, or under, or for the purposes of, any provision of this Act, wilfully makes a`
  line `statement which is false in any material particular, knowing it to be false, or wilfully omits to make a`
  line `material statement, shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to one year and`
  line `shall also be liable to fine.`
  line
  line `(2) Every credit information company or a credit institution or any specified user, wilfully,`
  line `performing any act or engaging in any practice, in breach of any of the principles referred to in section 20,`
  line `shall be punishable with fine not exceeding one crore rupees.`
  line
  line `(3) Any credit information company or credit institution or specified user wilfully providing to any`
  line `other credit information company or credit institution or specified user or borrower or client, as the case`
  line `may be, credit information which is false in any material particular, knowing it to be false, or wilfully`
  line `omits to make a material statement, shall be punishable with fine which may extend to one crore rupees.`
  line
  line `(4) Any person who contravenes any provision of this Act or of any rule or order made thereunder, or`
  line `obstructs the lawful exercise of any power conferred by or under this Act, or makes default in complying`
  line `with any requirement of this Act or of any rule or order made or direction issued thereunder, shall, if no`
  line `specific provision is made under this Act for punishment of such contravention, obstruction or default, be`
  line `punishable with fine which may extend to one lakh rupees and where a contravention or default is a`
  line `continuing one, with a further fine which may extend to five thousand rupees for every day during which`
  line `the contravention or default continues.`
  line
  line `(5) Where a contravention or default has been committed by a credit information company or credit`
  line `institution or specified user, as the case may be, every person who, at the time the contravention or default`
  line `was committed, was in charge of, and was responsible to the credit information company or credit`
  line `institution or specified user for the conduct of its business, shall be deemed to be guilty of the`
  line `contravention or default and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment provided in this Act if he proves that the contravention or default was committed without his`
  line `knowledge or that he exercised all due diligence to prevent the contravention or default.`
  line
  line `(6) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (5), where a contravention or default has been`
  line `committed by a credit information company or credit institution or specified user, as the case may be, and`
  line `it is proved that the same was committed with the consent or connivance of, or is attributable to any gross`
  line `negligence on the part of its chairperson, managing director, any other director, manager, secretary or`
  line `other officer of the credit information company or the credit institution, such chairperson, managing`
  line `director, any other director, manager, secretary or other officer shall also be deemed to be guilty of that`
  line `contravention or default and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means any body corporate and includes a firm or other association of individual,`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) "director", in relation to a firm, means a partner in the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (19344)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Cognizance of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00003_200530_1517807317795&sectionId=19344&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00003_200530_1517807317795
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) No court shall take cognizance of any offence committed by a`
  line `member of a credit information company and punishable under section 23 except upon a complaint in`
  line `writing made by an officer of the credit information company generally or specially authorised in writing`
  line `in this behalf by the credit information company or if so directed by the Reserve Bank so to do and no`
  line `court other than that of a Metropolitan Magistrate or a Judicial Magistrate of the first class or any court`
  line `superior thereto shall try any such offence.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this sub-section, "member of a credit information company" shall`
  line `mean a member referred to in section 15.`
  line
  line `(2) No court shall take cognizance of any offence committed by a credit information company`
  line `punishable under section 23 except upon a complaint in writing made by an officer of the Reserve Bank`
  line `generally or specially authorised in writing in this behalf by the Reserve Bank and no court other than that`
  line `of a Metropolitan Magistrate or a Judicial Magistrate of the first class or any court superior thereto shall`
  line `try any such offence.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (19345)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Power of Reserve Bank to impose penalty.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00003_200530_1517807317795&sectionId=19345&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00003_200530_1517807317795
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in section`
  line `23, if a contravention or default of the nature referred to in sub-section (2) of section 22 or sub-section (2)`
  line `or sub-section (3) or sub-section (4) of section 23, as the case may be, is made by a credit information`
  line `company or a credit institution then, the Reserve Bank may impose on such credit information company`
  line `or credit institution--`
  line
  line `(i) where the contravention is of the nature referred to in sub-section (2) of section 22, a penalty`
  line `not exceeding one lakh rupees;`
  line
  line `(ii) where the contravention is of the nature referred to in sub-section (2) or sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 23, a penalty not exceeding one crore rupees;`
  line
  line `(iii) where the contravention is of the nature referred to in sub-section (4) of section 23, a penalty`
  line `not exceeding one lakh rupees and where such contravention or default is continuing one, a further`
  line `penalty which may extend to five thousand rupees for every day, after the first, during which the`
  line `contravention or default continues.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purpose of adjudging the penalty under sub-section (1), the Reserve Bank shall serve`
  line `notice on credit information company or credit institution or specified user, as the case may be, requiring`
  line `it to show cause as to why the amount mentioned in the notice should not be imposed as penalty and a`
  line `reasonable opportunity of being heard shall also be given to such credit information company or credit`
  line `institution or specified user, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(3) No complaint shall be filed against credit information company or credit institution or specified`
  line `user, as the case may be, in any court of law in respect of any contravention or default in respect of which`
  line `any penalty has been imposed by the Reserve Bank under this section.`
  line
  line `(4) Any penalty imposed by the Reserve Bank under this Act shall be payable within a period of`
  line `fourteen days from the date on which notice issued by the Reserve Bank demanding payment of the sum`
  line `is served on the credit information company or credit institution or specified user, as the case may be, and`
  line `in the event of failure of such credit information company or credit institution or specified user to pay the`
  line `sum within such period, may be levied on a direction made by the principal civil court having jurisdiction`
  line `in the area where the registered office of the credit information company or credit institution or specified`
  line `user, being a company, is situated and in case of credit institution incorporated outside India, where its`
  line `principal place of business in India is situated:`
  line
  line `Provided that such direction under this sub-section shall be made only upon an application made in`
  line `this behalf to the court by the Reserve Bank.`
  line
  line `(5) The court which makes a direction under sub-section (4) shall issue a certificate mentioning`
  line `therein the sum payable by a credit information company or credit institution or specified user, as the case`
  line `may be, and every such certificate shall be enforceable in the same manner as if it were a decree made by`
  line `the court in a civil suit.`
  line
  line `(6) Where any complaint has been filed against credit information company or credit institution or`
  line `specified user, as the case may be, in any court in respect of the contravention or default of the nature`
  line `referred to in sub-section (2) of section 22 or sub-section (2) or sub-section (3) or sub-section (4) of section 23, then, no proceedings for the imposition of any penalty on the credit information company or`
  line `credit institution or specified user shall be taken under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (19346)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Application of fines.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00003_200530_1517807317795&sectionId=19346&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00003_200530_1517807317795
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `A court imposing any fine under this Act may direct that the whole or any`
  line `part thereof shall be applied in or towards payment of the costs of the proceedings, or for such purposes as`
  line `may be directed by the court.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (19347)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Power of Reserve Bank to specify maximum amount of fees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00003_200530_1517807317795&sectionId=19347&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00003_200530_1517807317795
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `The Reserve Bank may,`
  line `specify, by regulations the maximum amount of fees leviable under sub-section (3) of section 14 for`
  line `providing information to the specified users and for admissions of credit institutions or credit information`
  line `companies as a member of a credit information company.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (19348)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Disclosure of information before any court or tribunal or authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00003_200530_1517807317795&sectionId=19348&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00003_200530_1517807317795
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `No chairperson,`
  line `director, member, auditor, adviser, officer or other employee or agent employed in the business of a credit`
  line `information company or in the business of a specified user shall, except for the purposes of this Act or`
  line `when required to do so by any other law in force or court or tribunal or authority, disclose any`
  line `information to any person.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (19349)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Obligations as to fidelity and secrecy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00003_200530_1517807317795&sectionId=19349&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00003_200530_1517807317795
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every credit information company shall observe,`
  line `except as otherwise required by law, the practices and usages customary among credit information`
  line `companies and it shall not divulge any information relating to, or to the affairs of, its members or`
  line `specified users.`
  line
  line `(2) Every chairperson, director, member, auditor, adviser, officer or other employee of a credit`
  line `information company shall, before entering upon his duties, make a declaration of fidelity and secrecy in`
  line `the form, as may be prescribed in this regard.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section and section 30, the terms "practices and usages`
  line `customary" means such practices and usages which, are generally followed by credit information`
  line `companies or may develop in due course in relation to their functions, in pursuance of the provisions of`
  line `this Act, rules and regulations made and directions issued thereunder from time to time in pursuance`
  line thereof.
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (19350)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00003_200530_1517807317795&sectionId=19350&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00003_200530_1517807317795
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) No suit or other legal proceedings or prosecution`
  line `shall lie against the Reserve Bank or the Central Government or credit information company or credit`
  line `institution, or their chairperson, director, member, auditor, adviser, officer or other employee, or agent or`
  line `any person authorised by the Reserve Bank or the Central Government or credit information company or`
  line `credit institution to discharge any function under this Act, for any loss or damage caused or as is likely to`
  line `be caused by anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done, in pursuance of this Act or any`
  line `other law for the time being in force.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing contained in sub-section (1) shall affect the right of any person to claim damages against`
  line `a credit information company, a credit institution or their chairperson, director, member, auditor, adviser,`
  line `officer or other employee or agents, as the case may be, in respect of loss caused to him on account of any`
  line `such disclosure made by anyone of them and which is unauthorised or fraudulent or contrary to provisions`
  line `of this Act, or practices or usages customary among them.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (19351)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Bar of jurisdiction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00003_200530_1517807317795&sectionId=19351&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00003_200530_1517807317795
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `No court or authority shall have, or be entitled to exercise, any jurisdiction,`
  line `powers or authority, except the Supreme Court and a High Court exercising jurisdiction under articles 32,`
  line `226 and 227 of the Constitution, in relation to the matters referred to in sections 4, 5, 6, 7 and 18.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (19352)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Power of Reserve Bank to exempt in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00003_200530_1517807317795&sectionId=19352&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00003_200530_1517807317795
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, on the`
  line `recommendation of the Reserve Bank, by notification in the Official Gazette, direct that any or all of the`
  line `provisions of this Act shall not apply to any credit information company or a credit institution, as the case`
  line `may be, either generally or for such period and subject to such exceptions or modifications, as may be`
  line `mentioned in that notification.`
  line
  line `(2) A copy of every notification proposed to be issued under sub-section (1), shall be laid in draft`
  line `before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session`
  line `immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in`
  line `disapproving the issue of the notification or both Houses agree in making any modification in the`
  line `notification, the notification shall not be issued or, as the case may be, shall be issued only in such`
  line `modified form as may be agreed upon by both the Houses.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (19353)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Application of other laws not barred.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00003_200530_1517807317795&sectionId=19353&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00003_200530_1517807317795
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall be in addition to, and`
  line `not, save as provided under this Act, in derogation of, the provisions of the Companies Act,`
  line `1956 (1 of 1956) or any other law for the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33_a:
  sectionId (50214)
  sectionNo 33A
  orderNo 34
  title `Powers of Reserve Bank not to apply to International Financial Services Centre.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 50 of 2019, s. 33 and the second Schedule (date to be notified).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00003_200530_1517807317795&sectionId=50214&sectionno=33A&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00003_200530_1517807317795
obj_root_law_sections_33_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[33A. Powers of Reserve Bank not to apply to International Financial Services Centre.--`
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, the powers exercisable`
  line `by the Reserve Bank under this Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) shall not extend to an International Financial Services Centre set up under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 18 of the Special Economic Zones Act, 2005 (28 of 2005);`
  line
  line `(b) shall be exercisable by the International Financial Services Centres Authority established under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 4 of the International Financial Services Centres Authority Act, 2019,`
  line
  line `in so far as regulation of financial products, financial services and financial institutions that are permitted`
  line `in the International Financial Services Centres are concerned.]`
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (19354)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 35
  title `Amendment of certain enactments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00003_200530_1517807317795&sectionId=19354&sectionno=34&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00003_200530_1517807317795
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `The enactments mentioned in the Schedule to this Act`
  line `shall be amended in the manner specified therein.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (19355)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 36
  title `Removal of difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00003_200530_1517807317795&sectionId=19355&sectionno=35&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00003_200530_1517807317795
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of this Act,`
  line `the Central Government may, by order published in the Official Gazette, make such provisions not`
  line `inconsistent with the provisions of this Act as appear to it to be necessary or expedient for removing the`
  line `difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order shall be made under this section after the expiry of a period of two years from`
  line `the commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (19356)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 37
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00003_200530_1517807317795&sectionId=19356&sectionno=36&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00003_200530_1517807317795
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, after consultation with the Reserve`
  line `Bank, by notification in the Official Gazette, make rules to carry out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing powers, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the authority or tribunal which may be designated under sub-section (1) of section 7;`
  line
  line `(b) the steps to be taken by every credit information company or credit institution and specified`
  line `user for ensuring accuracy, completeness of data and protection of data from any loss or unauthorised`
  line `access or use or disclosure under section 19;`
  line
  line `(c) the form in which a declaration of fidelity and secrecy shall be made under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 29;`
  line
  line `(d) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made by the Central Government under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it`
  line `is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which`
  line `may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the`
  line `session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in`
  line `making any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall`
  line `thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that`
  line `any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done`
  line `under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (19357)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 38
  title `Power of Reserve Bank to make regulations THE SCHEDULE.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00003_200530_1517807317795&sectionId=19357&sectionno=37&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00003_200530_1517807317795
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Reserve Bank may make regulations`
  line `consistent with the provisions of this Act and the rules made thereunder to carry out the purposes of this`
  line Act.
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing powers, such regulations`
  line `may provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the persons or institutions which may be specified as specified users under clause (l) of`
  line `section 2;`
  line
  line `(b) the form in which application may be made under sub-section (1) of section 4 and the manner`
  line `of filing such application under that sub-section;`
  line
  line `(c) any other form of business in which a credit information company may engage under`
  line `clause (e) of sub-section (1) of section 14;`
  line
  line `(d) the form of notice for collection and furnishing of information procedure relating thereto and`
  line `purposes for which credit information may be provided under sub-sections (1) and (2) of section 17;`
  line
  line `(e) the principles and procedures relating to credit information which may be specified under`
  line `clause (f) of section 20;`
  line
  line `(f) the amount which may be required to be paid for obtaining copy of credit information under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 21;`
  line
  line `(g) the maximum amount of charges payable under section 27.`
  line
  line `(3) Every regulation, as soon as may be after it is made by the Reserve Bank, shall be forwarded to`
  line `the Central Government and that Government shall cause a copy of the same to be laid before each House`
  line `of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one`
  line `session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the regulation, or both Houses agree that the regulation should not be made, the regulation shall,`
  line `thereafter, have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that`
  line `any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done`
  line `under that regulation.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
